<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - DRIVETRAIN FAILURE ANALYSIS - TRANSMISSION COMPONENTS -
        SYNCHRONIZED TRANSMISSIONS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="9">
        <title>SYNCHRONIZED TRANSMISSIONS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>These transmissions are designed for first gear starts. The correct shifting procedure requires moving
                the shift lever in one smooth motion until the shift is completed. Failure to follow this practice can
                result in the blocking action of the synchronizer to become ineffective and gear clashing will result.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Failures Due to Improper Shifting</title>
            <para>Examples of failures due to improper shifting:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rounded corners on synchronizer clutching teeth (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300213">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300213" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300213" filename="../figg13/g1300213.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 13. Rounded Corners on Synchronizer Clutching Teeth</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clutch teeth on gears will become worn or chipped (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300214">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300214" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300214" filename="../figg13/g1300214.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 14. Worn or Chipped Clutch Teeth</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rounded teeth at the gear I.D. result in gear jumping (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300215">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300215" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300215" filename="../figg13/g1300215.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 15. Rounded Teeth at Gear I.D.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The soft brass synchronizer rings will become imbedded with metal chips from the
                    clutching teeth (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300216">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300216" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300216" filename="../figg13/g1300216.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 16. Synchronizer Rings Imbedded With Metal Chips</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Vibration Failures</title>
            <para>For vibration complaints in synchronized transmissions, refer to
                <hotlnk document="s13002_2.xml" xrefid="x1300201">VIBRATION
                    <xref refid="x1300201"/>
                </hotlnk>
                . Examples of vibration failures follow:
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mainshaft seizure of the fourth speed fluted diameter (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300217">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300217" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300217" filename="../figg13/g1300217.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 17. Mainshaft Seizure of Fourth Speed Fluted Diameter</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Severe seizure of both the third and fourth gear area (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300218">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300218" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300218" filename="../figg13/g1300218.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 18. Seizure of Third and Fourth Gear Area</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">High heat welded the hub to the mainshaft (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300219">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300219" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300219" filename="../figg13/g1300219.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 19. High Heat Welded Hub to Mainshaft</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Washer seized to the thrust face of its gear (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300220">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300220" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300220" filename="../figg13/g1300220.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 20. Washer Seized to Thrust Face of Gear</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Broken synchronizer pins (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300221">Figure 21</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300221" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300221" filename="../figg13/g1300221.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 21. Broken Synchronizer Pins</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
